  "text": "The watermark signal is a Gaussian random signal with zero mean that is independent both from the state noise w t and the measurement noise v t . Such an authentication watermark is expected to detect replay and integrity attacks modeled by the cyber adversary defined above. Now that the optimal control law u * t is equipped with the authentication signal Δu t , a detector -physically co-located with the controller -can be designed having the goal of generating alarms when an attack takes place. Towards this end, [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] propose to employ a χ 2 detector, a well-known category of real-time anomaly detectors classically used for fault detection in control systems [CITATION_3] , for the purpose of attack detection.",
